[2/30] P5 English EOY Ai Tong 2025 — Q9  Primary 5  (20.2s)
============================================================
STEM: "Brushing and flossing at least twice a day ___ important for healthy teeth," the dentist said.
  (1) were
  (2) was
  (3) are
  (4) is
ANSWER: 4

ELABORATION (646 chars):
This question tests **subject-verb agreement**, specifically when two actions form a single idea.

Even though "Brushing and flossing" lists two actions, they combine to form one single daily habit! Because this routine is considered one unit, it requires the **singular verb** "**is**" to state a general fact in the present tense.

**(1) were**: This uses the **wrong tense** (past) and has a **mismatched subject** (plural).
**(2) was**: This uses the **wrong tense** (past) instead of the present tense needed for a general truth.
**(3) are**: This has a **mismatched subject** because it is a plural verb, but the routine is one single idea.

