[3/30] P5 English EOY Ai Tong 2025 — Q10  Primary 5  (13.3s)
============================================================
STEM: ___ the traffic jam, Father was not late for work.
  (1) Since
  (2) Despite
  (3) Owing to
  (4) As a result of
ANSWER: 2

ELABORATION (689 chars):
This question tests **prepositions of contrast**, which are used to link a situation with an unexpected result.

**(2) Despite** is the correct answer because Father not being late is an unexpected result of a traffic jam. We use "despite" before a noun phrase like "the traffic jam" to show this contrasting idea.

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1) Since** is a **conjunction of reason**, which incorrectly makes the traffic jam the reason he was on time.
**(3) Owing to** is a **preposition of reason**, which also wrongly suggests the traffic jam caused him to not be late.
**(4) As a result of** shows **cause and effect**, but being on time is not the effect of a traffic jam!

