STEM: She has ___ experience in flying a plane as she has a pilot's licence.
  (1) few
  (2) most
  (3) many
  (4) some
ANSWER: 4

ELABORATION (576 chars):
This question tests **quantifiers with uncountable nouns**, which are words that tell us the amount of something we cannot count.

The word "experience" is an **uncountable noun**, so we must use the **quantifier** "some" in **(4)** to show she has a positive amount of practice flying planes.

**(1)** "few" is the wrong **quantifier** because it is only used with **plural countable nouns**.
**(2)** "most" is missing the article "the" to be grammatically correct here.
**(3)** "many" is the wrong **quantifier** because it is also only used with **plural countable nouns**.

