[6/30] P5 English EOY Henry Park 2025 — Q4  Primary 5  (11.6s)
============================================================
STEM: "I would have been punctual for school if I ___ up early this morning," I grumbled to my mother.
  (1) is waking
  (2) has woken
  (3) had woken
  (4) was waking
ANSWER: 3

ELABORATION (720 chars):
This question tests you on **Type 3 conditional sentences**, which talk about an imaginary past event that did not happen.

Since the main part of the sentence uses "would have been", the "if" clause must use the **past perfect tense** ("had woken") to show the action did not actually happen. That makes **(3)** the correct answer!

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1)** fails because "is waking" is the **present continuous tense**, which cannot describe a past event.
**(2)** fails because "has woken" is the **present perfect tense**, which does not fit this conditional structure.
**(4)** fails because "was waking" is the **past continuous tense**, but this rule strictly requires the **past perfect tense**.

